:     answered_questions: []\n29: ---\n30: \n31: # Verification Checklist: Fluid-responsive HTML report layout for create-diff\n32: \n33: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n34: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: checklist | v2.2 -->\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: <!-- ANCHOR:protocol -->\n39: ## Verification Protocol\n40: \n41: | Priority | Handling | Readiness Impact |\n42: |----------|----------|------------------|\n43: | **P0** | Hard blocker | Must pass before the packet is called complete |\n44: | **P1** | Required | Must pass or carry an explicit user-approved deferral |\n45: | **P2** | Optional | May remain for a later follow-up |\n46: \n47: > This packet is built and verified: the gates below are `[x]` with inline `[EVIDENCE: ...]` brackets. One gate is deferred — subjective visual acceptance in a real IDE webview (CHK-070) — because it is a user-runtime step not reproducible from this authoring environment; the rendered reports were delivered for that review.\n48: <!-- /ANCHOR:protocol -->\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: <!-- ANCHOR:pre-impl -->\n53: ## Pre-Implementation\n54: \n55: - [x] CHK-001 [P0] The safety-validator contract was read before authoring: `validate_report.py` inspects only `url(`/`@import`/`expression(` substrings, the tag/attr allowlist, and the exact CSP set. [EVIDENCE: `validate_report.py` `_style_problems`, `ALLOWED_TAGS`/`ALLOWED_ATTRS`, and `REQUIRED_CSP_DIRECTIVES` read before editing `_CSS`.]\n56: - [x] CHK-002 [P0] The phase-008 pinned literals and contrast-token regex boundaries were enumerated so the fluid layer preserves them. [EVIDENCE: pinned set enumerated — `.sxs{min-width:`, `.diff-scroll:focus-visible`, legend + `mark.wd` decorations, first `:root{…}` + dark block with `#hex` tokens.]\n57: - [x] CHK-003 [P1] The IDE-width envelope and reference fluid system were digested; container units chosen over viewport units. [EVIDENCE: `cqi` on `<main>` chosen over `vw` because a webview viewport can be the pane or the editor.]\n58: <!-- /ANCHOR:pre-impl -->\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: <!-- ANCHOR:code-quality -->\n63: ## CODE QUALITY\n64: \n65: - [x] CHK-010 [P0] The fluid layer is expressed as named semantic tokens (`--fs-0` base + `--fs-code`/`--rhythm`/`--measure`), retunable from one place. [EVIDENCE: the scale derives from `--fs-0` plus named tokens; a single edit retunes the whole system.]\n66: - [x] CHK-011 [P0] All added values are parenthesis-only so the contrast-token `:root{[^}]*}` regex is unaffected. [EVIDENCE: `clamp()`/`calc()`/`min()` tokens contain no `}`; `LegendContrast` token capture still reads `--text`/`--add-inline`/`--del-inline`.]\n67: - [x] CHK-012 [P1] No markup change; the container is established purely via CSS on the existing `<main>`. [EVIDENCE: `render_report` markup byte-unchanged; only `_CSS` edited.]\n68: <!-- /ANCHOR:code-quality -->\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: <!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n73: ## TESTING\n74: \n75: - [x] CHK-020 [P0] REQ-001 the fluid layer is always on and container-keyed. [EVIDENCE: rendered output carries `container-type:inline-size`, 4 `cqi` tokens, 2 `@container report` blocks; `test_fluid_type_layer_is_container_keyed` passes.]\n76: - [x] CHK-021 [P0] REQ-002 the safety-validator contract is unbroken. [EVIDENCE: `_CSS` substring scan → `url(` 0 / `@import` 0 / `expression(` 0; no inline `style=`; CSP `<meta>` byte-identical; `validate_report.py` on both views → PASS (exit 0).]\n77: - [x] CHK-022 [P0] REQ-003 phase-008 accessibility guarantees preserved. [EVIDENCE: `.sxs{min-width:` (60rem floor), `.diff-scroll:focus-visible`, `.legend mark.wd{color:var(--text)}`, `mark.wd.add/.del` decorations, light/dark contrast tokens all unchanged; `LegendContrast` + side-by-side scroll tests green.]\n78: - [x] CHK-023 [P1] REQ-004 IDE-width tuning with no comfortable-width regression. [EVIDENCE: each `--fs-*` max endpoint equals the prior fixed size (`--fs-0`→`1rem`, `--fs-code`→`13px`); `test_byte_reproducible` holds.]\n79: - [x] CHK-024 [P1] REQ-006 the layer is regression-locked; the suite is green. [EVIDENCE: `python3 -m unittest test_create_diff` → Ran 40 tests, OK (39 prior + 1 new).]\n80: <!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: <!-- ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n85: ## Fix Completeness\n86: \n87: - [x] CHK-030 [P0] The container context, fluid token set, and both `@container` refinements are all present in `_CSS`. [EVIDENCE: `container-type:inline-size`, `--fs-*`/`--rhythm`/`--measure` tokens, and 2 `@container report` blocks all present.]\n88: - [x] CHK-031 [P0] The `table.diff` `font` shorthand was converted to longhand so the fluid `font-size` composes with `var()`. [EVIDENCE: `table.diff` uses `font-family`/`font-size:var(--fs-code)`/`line-height` longhand.]\n89: - [x] CHK-032 [P1] The prose measure split leaves the summary table at its original `72rem` width. [EVIDENCE: `.summary-sec{max-width:72rem}` retained; only prose blocks moved to `--measure`.]\n90: <!-- /ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: <!-- ANCHOR:security -->\n95: ## Security\n96: \n97: - [x] CHK-040 [P0] No new network, font, image, or external reference is introduced; the report stays self-contained under the existing CSP. [EVIDENCE: no `url(`/`@import`/`@font-face`; system font stacks retained; CSP `<meta>` unchanged.]\n98: - [x] CHK-041 [P0] No inline `style=` attribute and no `<script` substring introduced. [EVIDENCE: `test_zero_js_and_exact_csp` green; validator `style=` rejection not triggered.]\n99: <!-- /ANCHOR:security -->\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: <!-- ANCHOR:docs -->\n104: ## Documentation\n105: \n106: - [x] CHK-050 [P1] `spec.md`/`plan.md`/`tasks.md`/`implementation-summary.md` are consistent; status reads Complete. [EVIDENCE: status Complete across the spec/plan/tasks/implementation-summary frontmatter and the spec + implementation-summary `Status` rows.]\n107: - [x] CHK-051 [P1] The 12px narrow-pane type floor is documented as a single-value tunable, not silently accepted. [EVIDENCE: `implementation-summary.md` Known Limitations #1 records the `--fs-code`/`--text-caption` floor tunable.]\n108: <!-- /ANCHOR:docs -->\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: <!-- ANCHOR:file-org -->\n113: ## File Organization\n114: \n115: - [x] CHK-060 [P1] The change is confined to `create_diff.py` `_CSS` + one test in `test_create_diff.py`; no other renderer surface touched. [EVIDENCE: only `_CSS` and `test_create_diff.py` modified; markup, CSP, and engine untouched.]\n116: - [x] CHK-061 [P1] Child holds the Level 2 document set; parent stays a lean phase parent. [EVIDENCE: `010-fluid-responsive-report/` holds `spec.md`/`plan.md`/`tasks.md`/`checklist.md`/`implementation-summary.md` (5/5) plus `description.json`/`graph-metadata.json`; the 033 parent keeps only the lean trio.]\n117: <!-- /ANCHOR:file-org -->\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: <!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\n122: ## Verification Summary\n123: \n124: | Gate | State | Evidence |\n125: |------|-------|----------|\n126: | Always-on container-keyed fluid layer (REQ-001) | VERIFIED | `container-type:inline-size` + 4 `cqi` tokens + 2 `@container report` blocks rendered |\n127: | Safety-validator contract (REQ-002) | VERIFIED | `url(`/`@import`/`expression(` 0/0/0; CSP byte-identical; `validate_report.py` both views exit 0 |\n128: | Phase-008 accessibility preserved (REQ-003) | VERIFIED | scroll floor, focus-visible, legend, mark decorations, contrast tokens all byte-unchanged |\n129: | IDE-width tuning, no regression (REQ-004) | VERIFIED | token max endpoints equal prior fixed sizes; `test_byte_reproducible` holds |\n130: | Clean iteration hooks (REQ-005) | VERIFIED | scale retunable from `--fs-0` + named semantic tokens |\n131: | Regression-locked, suite green (REQ-006) | VERIFIED | `test_create_diff` → 40 tests OK |\n132: | Strict validation (this child) | VERIFIED | `validate.sh 010-fluid-responsive-report --strict` → Errors 0 |\n133: | Live IDE-webview visual acceptance (CHK-070) | DEFERRED | user-runtime step; rendered artifacts delivered for review |\n134: \n135: **Verification Date**: 2026-07-16 (structural + test verification; live webview visual acceptance deferred — see CHK-070)\n136: <!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: <!-- ANCHOR:manual -->\n141: ## Manual Acceptance (operator)\n142: \n143: - [ ] CHK-070 [P1] Visual acceptance in a real IDE webview: open a report in a narrow (~480–700px) pane and confirm the 12px code/caption floor and shrunk headings are acceptable (raise the `--fs-code`/`--text-caption` clamp floor if not — a single-value edit). DEFERRED: not reproducible from the authoring environment; the rendered unified + side-by-side artifacts were delivered for review.\n144: <!-- /ANCHOR:manual -->\n\n(End of file - total 144 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Verification Checklist: Fluid-responsive HTML report layout for create-diff\"\ndescription: \"P0/P1 verification gates for the create-diff fluid report layer: always-on container-keyed fluid type, safety-validator contract unbroken, phase-008 accessibility preserved, IDE-width tuning with no comfortable-width regression, clean iteration hooks, and a regression-locking test with the full suite green.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"fluid responsive report checklist\"\n  - \"create diff container query gates\"\n  - \"diff report css verification\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"verification\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-16T05:42:31Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude\"\n    recent_action: \"Applied the fluid layer and locked it with a regression test\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Commit the renderer change + this phase and push to v4\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files:\n      - \"spec.md\"\n      - \"plan.md\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-