{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784210525538,"sessionID":"ses_094c57e18ffemFIYitl0QMkdbq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_XfsZxUJ4gvyDnz1fzb4l7S9i","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report/review/lineages/sol/deep-review-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report/review/lineages/sol/deep-review-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Review Strategy - Fluid Responsive Report\n2: \n3: ## 1. TOPIC\n4: Review `.opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report` and the 45 files declared by its `goal-file-manifest.txt`.\n5: \n6: ## 2. REVIEW CHARTER\n7: - Target: completed Level 2 spec packet and its declared create-diff implementation, documentation, command, catalog, and playbook surfaces.\n8: - Dimensions: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability.\n9: - Core protocols: `spec_code`, `checklist_evidence`.\n10: - Applicable overlays: `feature_catalog_code`, `playbook_capability`.\n11: - Resource Map Coverage: `resource-map.md` not present; skipping coverage gate.\n12: \n13: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n14: <!-- ANCHOR:review-dimensions -->\n15: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n16: - [ ] correctness\n17: - [ ] traceability\n18: - [ ] maintainability\n19: \n20: <!-- /ANCHOR:review-dimensions -->\n21: \n22: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n23: - Implementing fixes or changing any target file.\n24: - Expanding review beyond the manifest, canonical packet documents, and directly named evidence.\n25: - Performing subjective live IDE-webview acceptance that requires an operator runtime.\n26: \n27: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n28: - Legal convergence after all dimensions and core protocols are covered and stabilized, or iteration 10.\n29: - Any terminal infrastructure error that prevents coherent state production.\n30: \n31: ## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n32: <!-- ANCHOR:completed-dimensions -->\n33: ## 4. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n34: - [x] security\n35: \n36: <!-- /ANCHOR:completed-dimensions -->\n37: \n38: ## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n39: <!-- ANCHOR:running-findings -->\n40: ## 5. RUNNING FINDINGS\n41: - P0 (Blockers): 1\n42: - P1 (Required): 1\n43: - P2 (Suggestions): 1\n44: - Resolved: 0\n45: \n46: <!-- /ANCHOR:running-findings -->\n47: \n48: ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n49: - Initialization: goal-file manifest provides an explicit, ordered review boundary.\n50: - Iteration 001: Direct comparison of the renderer CSS, focused regression test, and governing fallback requirements exposed one active compatibility defect and one test-lock gap.\n51: - Iteration 002: Direct renderer/validator/test reads supported the escaping and CSP boundaries; tracing manifest data to the cleanup unlink sink plus a contained reproduction proved one path-traversal deletion blocker.\n52: \n53: ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n54: - Memory trigger transport closed before returning context; canonical packet docs are the continuity source.\n55: - Iteration 001: The passing substring regression test cannot validate unsupported-unit CSS semantics or prove both named-container refinements remain connected.\n56: - Iteration 002: Cleanup trusts each manifest `blob` value without basename or resolved-path containment validation, allowing a crafted store to delete a writable file outside the disposable snapshot tree.\n57: \n58: ## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n59: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n60: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n61: ### `checklist_evidence`: not expanded because the strategy marks this approach BLOCKED. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n62: - What was tried: `checklist_evidence`: not expanded because the strategy marks this approach BLOCKED.\n63: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n64: - D