{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784210565480,"sessionID":"ses_094c57e18ffemFIYitl0QMkdbq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_RETQnpqolThVTq3NfxYVTEZL","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report/review/lineages/sol/logs/fanout-lineage.out"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report/review/lineages/sol/logs/fanout-lineage.out</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1784210283891,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f6b385d6f001bOSp3oQR9MEHTv\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f6b384269001EDKZXyGxmvCeKo\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n2: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1784210291433,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f6b386d3e001qynEfnNnNeog5F\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f6b384269001EDKZXyGxmvCeKo\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"review_target: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report\\nreview_target_type: spec-folder\\nreview_dimensions: all\\nspec_folder: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report\\nexecution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\\nlineage_mode: auto\\nartifact_dir: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report/review/lineages/sol\\nsession_id: fanout-sol-1784210154469-yt14nz\\nSKILL ROUTING: User directed -> deep-review with cli-opencode executor `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784210287934,\"end\":1784210291431},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_0f1205be1dbfd8bc016a58e36faafc8191b223b352f9e456ab\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n3: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784210291740,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"skill\",\"callID\":\"call_Lf75Is26IpjfUF2sGMxXF6mC\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"name\":\"deep-review\"},\"output\":\"<skill_content name=\\\"deep-review\\\">\\n# Skill: deep-review\\n\\n<!-- Note: Task is for the command executor (loop management); @deep-review agent is LEAF-only (no Task). No WebFetch: review is code-only. -->\\n\\n<!-- Keywords: deep-review, iterative-review, review-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, review-agent, JSONL-state, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, release-readiness, spec-alignment -->\\n\\n# Autonomous Deep Review Loop\\n\\nIterative code review and quality auditing protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, convergence detection, and severity-weighted findings (P0/P1/P2).\\n\\nRuntime path resolution:\\n- OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\\n- Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\\n\\nConvergence threshold semantics and sibling-parity notes (deep-review 0.10 vs deep-research 0.05 vs deep-ai-council 0.20) live in `references/convergence/convergence.md` §1 under \\\"Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\\\".\\n\\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\\n\\n### When to Use This Skill\\n\\nUse this skill when:\\n- Code quality audit requiring multiple rounds across different review dimensions\\n- Spec folder validation requiring cross-reference checks between docs and implementation\\n- Release readiness check before shipping a feature or component\\n- Finding misalignments between spec documents and actual code\\n- Verifying cross-references across documentation, agents, commands, and code\\n- Iterative review where each dimension's findings inform subsequent dimensions\\n- Unattended or overnight audit sessions\\n\\n### When NOT to Use\\n\\n- Simple single-pass code review (use `sk-code`'s code-review mode instead)\\n- Known issues that just need fixing (go directly to implementation)\\n- Implementation tasks (use `sk... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n4: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784210291767,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"skill\",\"callID\":\"call_CC1O8eisUtLs1XPwQo3wcAsD\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"name\":\"cli-opencode\"},\"output\":\"<skill_content name=\\\"cli-opencode\\\">\\n# Skill: cli-opencode\\n\\n<!-- Keywords: opencode, opencode-cli, opencode-run, cross-ai, spec-kit-runtime, plugin-runtime, parallel-sessions, share-url, detached-session, agent-delegation, deepseek, openai, minimax, minimax-coding-plan, minimax-m3, token-plan, xiaomi, xiaomi-token-plan, xiaomi-token-plan-ams, xiaomi-api, xiaomi-direct, mimo, mimo-v2.5-pro, mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed, ultraspeed, glm-5.2, zai-coding-plan, z.ai-coding-plan, glm-coding-plan -->\\n\\n# OpenCode CLI Orchestrator - Full-Runtime Cross-AI Dispatch\\n\\n> **CRITICAL — SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED**\\n>\\n> This skill dispatches to the OpenCode CLI binary (`opencode`). If the agent currently reading this skill is itself running inside OpenCode (TUI / acp / serve / run modes — detection signals listed in §2), the skill MUST refuse to load and return the documented error message instead of generating any `opencode` invocation. The only exception is an explicit \\\"parallel detached\\\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory.\\n>\\n> A running CLI skill never dispatches itself. The cli-X skills are for **cross-AI delegation only** — never self-invocation.\\n\\nOrchestrate OpenCode's `opencode run` from external AI assistants (Claude Code, OpenCode, raw shell) AND from inside an existing OpenCode session for parallel detached workers. Three documented use cases keep the cycle risk explicit while giving every dispatch path a copy-paste invocation shape.\\n\\n**Core Principle**: The calling AI stays the conductor. Delegate to OpenCode for what it does best — full plugin, skill, MCP, and Spec Kit Memory runtime in a one-shot dispatch. Validate and integrate the output.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. WHEN... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n5: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784210301008,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"mk-spec-memory_memory_match_triggers\",\"callID\":\"call_jaEVnvMt0tYOxYKkkaBIunJV\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"error\",\"input\":{\"prompt\":\"Execute detached deep-review loop for spec folder .opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report using lineage artifact directory review/lineages/sol, session fanout-sol-1784210154469-yt14nz, convergence stop policy, max 10 iterations.\"},\"error\":\"MCP error -32000: Connection closed\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784210291601,\"end\":1784210301005}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_0f1205be1dbfd8bc016a58e373618081919092487f02dbb8dd\"}},\"id\":\"prt_f6b387b03001FAux7quBHy7Q4n\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f6b384269001EDKZXyGxmvCeKo\"}}\n6: {\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1784210302350,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f6b38a588001uIb6XhhYh1zaJ5\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f6b384269001EDKZXyGxmvCeKo\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":33086,\"input\":32676,\"output\":280,\"reasoning\":130,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":0}},\"cost\":0}}\n7: {\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1784210307097,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f6b38b817001JKtpdRUDBgv3iU\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f6b38ab470015r2LVrLHrFOyON\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n8: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1784210311105,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f6b38c5cc001VMsfa5zOXforlK\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f6b38ab470015r2LVrLHrFOyON\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The detached-session exception applies, and the requested directory is the sole write boundary. The memory trigger service is unavailable (`MCP error -32000: Connection closed`); workflow execution can proceed from the pre-bound packet state and canonical YAML.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784210310604,\"end\":1784210311103},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_01df3d0a51ecc143016a58e3868d1c81918e3853d75e04d638\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n9: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784210313375,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"todowrite\",\"callID\":\"call_7mhVyExkphbPc4B7wxJqR9zg\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"todos\":[{\"content\":\"Load the canonical deep-review YAML, protocol, and detached lineage state\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"priority\":\"high\"},{\"content\":\"Run phase_init with the supplied pre-bound artifact directory\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"priority\":\"high\"},{\"content\":\"Run review iterations until legal convergence or iteration 10\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"priority\":\"high\"},{\"content\":\"Run phase_synthesis and verify all lineage artifacts\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"priority\":\"high\"}]},\"output\":\"[\\n  {\\n    \\\"content\\\": \\\"Load the canonical deep-review YAML, protocol, and detached lineage state\\\",\\n    \\\"status\\\": \\\"in_progress\\\",\\n    \\\"priority\\\": \\\"high\\\"\\n  },\\n  {\\n    \\\"content\\\": \\\"Run phase_init with the supplied pre-bound artifact directory\\\",\\n    \\\"status\\\": \\\"pending\\\",\\n    \\\"priority\\\": \\\"high\\\"\\n  },\\n  {\\n    \\\"content\\\": \\\"Run review iterations until legal convergence or iteration 10\\\",\\n    \\\"status\\\": \\\"pending\\\",\\n    \\\"priority\\\": \\\"high\\\"\\n  },\\n  {\\n    \\\"content\\\": \\\"Run phase_synthesis and verify all lineage artifacts\\\",\\n    \\\"status\\\": \\\"pending\\\",\\n    \\\"priority\\\": \\\"high\\\"\\n  }\\n]\",\"metadata\":{\"todos\":[{\"content\":\"Load the canonical deep-review YAML, protocol, and detached lineage state\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"priority\":\"high\"},{\"content\":\"Run phase_init with the supplied pre-bound artifact directory\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"priority\":\"high\"},{\"content\":\"Run review iterations until legal convergence or iteration 10\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"priority\":\"high\"},{\"content\":\"Run phase_synthesis and verify all lineage artifacts\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"priority\":\"high\"}],\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"4 todos\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784210313372,\"end\":1784210313374}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_01df3d0a51ecc143016a58e38714788191bd467b523839850e\"}},\"id\":\"prt_f6b38c7c3001... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n10: {\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1784210314915,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f6b38d6a1001RdbC47stJwuqIO\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f6b38ab470015r2LVrLHrFOyON\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":41425,\"input\":41161,\"output\":164,\"reasoning\":100,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":0}},\"cost\":0}}\n11: {\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1784210326648,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f6b390476001k0jhJd2vLyJuiR\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f6b38daf6001ctsmSvbutG8472\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"snapshot\":\"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n12: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784210326882,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_JddoCqnmlP3hlF63XR5F60Hq\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n2: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n4: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\\n5: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n6: role: Deep Review Loop Manager\\n7: purpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\\n8: action: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\\n9: operating_mode:\\n10:   workflow: iterative_loop\\n11:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\\n12:   workflow_execution: autonomous\\n13:   approvals: none\\n14:   tracking: progressive_review_state\\n15:   validation: convergence_detection\\n16: \\n17: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n18: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n20: operating_principles:\\n21:   core: \\\"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\\\"\\n22:   approach: \\\"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\\\"\\n23:   mandate: \\\"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\\\"\\n24: \\n25: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n26: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\\n27: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n28: user_inputs:\\n29:   r... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n13: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784210327103,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_noh4GqDLOISKp93xn6ax2cKF\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Review Quick Reference\\n3: description: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"deep review quick reference\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"review loop cheat sheet\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"p0 p1 p2 severity ladder\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"release readiness verdicts\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"review loop troubleshooting\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: normal\\n11: contextType: general\\n12: version: 1.11.0.16\\n13: ---\\n14: \\n15: # Deep Review Quick Reference\\n16: \\n17: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n22: \\n23: ### Purpose\\n24: \\n25: Use this quick reference when you need the command shape, artifact names, convergence rules, and synthesis outputs for the autonomous deep-review loop without loading the full protocol references.\\n26: \\n27: ### When to Use\\n28: \\n29: - Looking up the canonical `/deep:review` invocation without re-reading the full SKILL.md.\\n30: - Confirming default thresholds, verdicts, or release-readiness states at a glance.\\n31: - Refreshing the artifact-name and packet-file checklist before a manual orchestration pass.\\n32: - Triaging a stuck loop and need the fastest path to convergence semantics.\\n33: \\n34: ### Commands\\n35: \\n36: | Command | Description |\\n37: |---------|-------------|\\n38: | `/deep:review:auto \\\"target\\\"` | Run autonomous review (no approval gates) |\\n39: | `/deep:review:confirm \\\"target\\\"` | Run ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n14: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784210327248,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_D6gNunT3IKcD9Hj36mE7Mh6V\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n3: description: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"deep review loop protocol\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"review iteration lifecycle\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"review loop initialization\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"review auto resume\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"review synthesis phase\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: version: 1.11.0.29\\n13: ---\\n14: \\n15: # Deep Review Loop Protocol\\n16: \\n17: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n22: \\n23: ### Purpose\\n24: \\n25: The deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\\n26: \\n27: ### When to Use\\n28: \\n29: - Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\\n30: - Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\\n31: - Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\\n32: - Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\\n33: \\n34: ```\\n35: ┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\\n36: ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n15: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784210327272,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_2eE0vtzChROmzIF01TdInxX1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Review Convergence\\n3: description: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"review convergence detection\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"severity weighted stop ratio\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"legal stop gate bundle\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"review stuck detection\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"composite convergence vote\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: version: 1.11.0.22\\n13: ---\\n14: \\n15: # Deep Review Convergence\\n16: \\n17: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n22: \\n23: ### Purpose\\n24: \\n25: Convergence detection determines when the autonomous review loop should stop iterating. After every iteration the orchestrator evaluates three possible outcomes:\\n26: \\n27: | Outcome | Meaning |\\n28: |---------|---------|\\n29: | **CONTINUE** | More review work is expected to yield meaningful new findings. Dispatch the next iteration. |\\n30: | **STOP** | The review has reached saturation. Proceed to synthesis and verdict. |\\n31: | **STUCK_RECOVERY** | No progress detected for consecutive iterations. Attempt a recovery strategy before deciding. |\\n32: \\n33: Convergence is checked **after** each iteration completes and **before** the next iteration is dispatched. The check consumes the full JSONL state history and the current dimension... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n16: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784210327353,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_L52ovfWY9t02hwT3llhPb1cZ\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Review State Format\\n3: description: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"deep review state format\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"deep review config schema\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"review severity weights\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"file protection levels\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"review iteration file structure\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: version: 1.11.0.28\\n13: ---\\n14: \\n15: # Deep Review State Format\\n16: \\n17: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n22: \\n23: The deep review loop uses 8 state files under the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` owned by the target spec:\\n24: \\n25: | File | Format | Mutability |\\n26: |------|--------|------------|\\n27: | `deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Immutable after init |\\n28: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSON Lines | Append-only |\\n29: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Auto-generated reducer state |\\n30: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Updated each iteration |\\n31: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated (read-only) |\\n32: | `.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Created/deleted by user |\\n33: | `review-report.md` | Markdown | Updated at synthesis |\\n34: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Write-once |\\n35: \\n36: ```text\\n37: {artifact_dir}/\\n38:   deep-review... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n17: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784210327373,\"sessionID\":\"ses_094c7bf79ffepdruFg8KGB86sW\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_b0WVEvq7GmPRdSfVITC8ybU1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report/review/lineages/sol\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report/review/lineages/sol</path>\\n<type>directory</type>\\n<entries>\\n.executor-state/\\ndeep-review-config.json\\ndeep-review-dashboard.md\\ndeep-review-findings-registry.json\\ndeep-review-state.jsonl\\ndeep-review-strategy.md\\ndeltas/\\niterations/\\nlogs/\\nprompts/\\n\\n(10 entries)\\n</entries>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\".executor-state/\\ndeep-review-config.json\\ndeep-review-dashboard.md\\ndeep-review-findings-registry.json\\ndeep-review-state.jsonl\\ndeep-review-strategy.md\\ndeltas/\\niterations/\\nlogs/\\nprompts/\",\"truncated\":false,\"loaded\":[],\"display\":{\"type\":\"directory\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report/review/lineages/sol\",\"entries\":[\".executor-state/\",\"deep-review-config.json\",\"deep-review-dashboard.md\",\"deep-review-findings-registry.json\",\"deep-review-state.jsonl\",\"deep-r