stores\",\"manifest trust boundary\",\"all user-writable files reachable by the process\"],\"content_hash\":\"0c69843c1ef5a5194ac0ea92716c36b014365e1dc7e1ab943e17ab9d3c089fa1\",\"type\":\"claim-adjudication\",\"findingId\":\"P0-001\",\"claim\":\"cleanup trusts manifest blob paths, allowing a crafted snapshot manifest to unlink a writable file outside the selected state store\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/scripts/create_diff.py:1178-1184\",\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/scripts/create_diff.py:1431-1448\",\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/feature-catalog/snapshot-lifecycle/snapshot-state-management.md:20-28\",\"temporary reproduction: cleanupExit=0, victimExistsAfterCleanup=false\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Searched for schema checks, basename restrictions, resolved-path containment, symlink/path-traversal defenses, mandatory dry-run, and an explicit trusted-store precondition; none was found. Dry-run is optional.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"The store is intended to be local and disposable, and exploitation requires a crafted/corrupt manifest plus a real cleanup invocation; this lowers reachability but does not contain deletion to the store.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P0\",\"confidence\":0.99,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade only after current code rejects non-basename blob values and proves the resolved target remains beneath the selected snapshot subdirectory, or authoritative threat-model evidence makes all accepted stores integrity-protected.\",\"hunter\":\"Traced all manifest-derived filesystem joins and isolated the destructive sink.\",\"skeptic\":\"Tested the local-only, disposable-store, and optional-dry-run explanations against source and docs.\",\"referee\":\"Executable reproduction proved deletion outside the store; destructive data loss sustains P0.\"}],\"carriedAdjudications\":[{\"findingId\":\"P1-001\",\"claim\":\"Unsupported cqi makes the variable-backed consuming declarations invalid instead of selecting the clamp bounds, violating the specified fixed-size fallback.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/scripts/create_diff.py:720-727\",\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/scripts/create_diff.py:731-738\",\".opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report/spec.md:137\",\".opencode/specs/sk-doc/033-create-diff-mode/010-fluid-responsive-report/spec.md:153\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Checked for fixed fallback declarations, @supports guards, and containment by the fixed body font. The body rule prevents total loss of readable text but does not preserve prior per-surface sizes.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"Modern Chromium IDE webviews support container query units, confining the defect to the promised unsupported-engine path.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.95,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade only if the fallback requirement is removed or engine-level evidence proves unsupported cqi in these var()-substituted clamp() values resolves to the bounds.\"}],\"traceabilityChecks\":[{\"protocol\":\"spec_code\",\"status\":\"blocked\",\"reason\":\"Iteration-001 approach is marked BLOCKED; not retried.\"},{\"protocol\":\"checklist_evidence\",\"status\":\"blocked\",\"reason\":\"Strategy marks this approach BLOCKED; not retried.\"},{\"protocol\":\"security_contract\",\"status\":\"fail\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/scripts/create_diff.py:1431-1448\",\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/feature-catalog/snapshot-lifecycle/snapshot-state-management.md:20-28\"]}],\"newFindingsRatio\":0.625,\"noveltyJustification\":\"One new P0 contributes weight 10 against prior accumulated weight 6 plus current weight 10: 10/16=0.625. P1-001 is corrected carry-forward and contributes no new or refinement weight.\",\"budgetProfile\":\"verify\",\"edgeCases\":[\"Exploit requires a crafted/corrupt manifest and non-dry-run cleanup.\",\"Dry-run exposes but does not contain the escaped target.\",\"Corrected P1-001 packet is administrative carry-forward, not a new finding.\"],\"integrationEvidence\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/scripts/create_diff.py renderer and snapshot cleanup\",\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/scripts/validate_report.py safety validator\",\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/scripts/test_create_diff.py hostile-content and CSP tests\",\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/feature-catalog/snapshot-lifecycle/snapshot-state-management.md cleanup contract\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"renderer HTML injection across inspected source and metadata paths\",\"CSP-preservation or validator-allowlist bypass\",\"P1 downgrade for P0-001 after reproduced out-of-store deletion\"],\"reviewDepthApplicability\":{\"version\":\"v2\",\"applicable\":true,\"reason\":\"Security review covered renderer, validator, tests, and destructive state operations.\"},\"targetSelection\":{\"declaredScopeCount\":45,\"selectedFiles\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/scripts/create_diff.py\",\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/scripts/test_create_diff.py\",\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-diff/scripts/validate_report.py\"],\"selectionReason\":\"Rendered prompt named the producer, hostile-content tests, validator boundary, and unsafe state operations; exact integration docs were added for contract evidence.\"},\"searchCoverage\":{\"requiredBugClasses\":[\"HTML injection\",\"CSP/validator bypass\",\"unsafe file/state operations\"],\"covered\":[\"HTML injection\",\"CSP/validator bypass\",\"unsafe file/state operations\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"HTML injection\",\"CSP/validator bypass\"],\"deferred\":[],\"blocked\":[],\"graphCoverageMode\":\"direct-file-evidence\"},\"searchLedger\":[{\"action\":\"renderer escape-flow inspection\",\"result\":\"clean\"},{\"action\":\"CSP and validator allowlist inspection\",\"result\":\"clean\"},{\"action\":\"hostile-content and conformance test inspection\",\"result\":\"clean\"},{\"action\":\"manifest-to-cleanup destructive sink inspection and reproduction\",\"result\":\"P0-001